{"questionId":"9084666","questionHtml":"<p>Two long parallel wires X and Y carry equal currents <em>I</em>. The magnetic force exerted per unit length of each wire is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></em>.</p>\n<p>The current in X is halved and the current in Y is doubled. What is the force per unit length of each wire after the change?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:549px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:26px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:26px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:253.234px;text-align:center;height:26px;\"><strong>Force per unit length of X</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:251.766px;text-align:center;height:26px;\"><strong>Force per unit length of Y</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:29px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:253.234px;text-align:center;height:29px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:251.766px;text-align:center;height:29px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:41px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:41px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:253.234px;text-align:center;height:41px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:251.766px;text-align:center;height:41px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:41px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:41px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:253.234px;text-align:center;height:41px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:251.766px;text-align:center;height:41px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:32px;\">\n<td style=\"width:47px;height:32px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:253.234px;text-align:center;height:32px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:251.766px;text-align:center;height:32px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084666","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.15","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Two long parallel wires X and Y carry equal currents I. The magnetic force exerted per unit length of each wire is F. The current in X is halved and the current in Y is doubled. Wh","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"15","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D. Fields","D.3 Motion in electromagnetic fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}